🐳 Node.js Docker Image Optimization Project
📌 Overview

This project explains the difference between an unoptimized Docker image and an optimized Docker image using Node.js. It shows how Dockerfile design affects image size, performance, and security.

📦 Docker Image Comparison

We created two Docker images:

❌ Unoptimized Image → uses full Node.js setup
✅ Optimized Image → uses lightweight Alpine setup
❌ 1. Unoptimized Docker Image
Dockerfile
FROM node:18

WORKDIR /app

COPY . .

RUN npm install

EXPOSE 3000

CMD ["npm", "start"]
🔴 Explanation
Uses full Node.js (Debian-based) image → large size
Copies entire project (may include unnecessary files)
Installs both development and production dependencies
No optimization or cleanup
📉 Result
Large image size (700MB – 1GB+)
Slow build process
Not suitable for production
✅ 2. Optimized Docker Image
Dockerfile
FROM node:18-alpine

WORKDIR /app

COPY package*.json ./

RUN npm install --omit=dev

COPY . .

USER node

EXPOSE 3000

CMD ["npm", "start"]
🟢 Explanation
Uses lightweight Alpine Linux base image
Installs only production dependencies (--omit=dev)
Copies dependency files first (better caching)
Runs container as non-root user (more secure)
📉 Result
Small image size (~100–200MB)
Faster build and deployment
Secure and production-ready


